# Project Documentation Structure

All docs live in `/docs`. Each document has a single responsibility; no overlap or duplication.

| Document | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| **user-flow.md** | Application behavioral flow from user perspective: entry points, navigation, screen/state transitions, decision branches, auth boundaries, error states, session lifecycle. No UI styling, schema, or implementation. |
| **prd.md** | What the system must do and why: problem statement, target users, scope, functional requirements, constraints, acceptance criteria, success metrics. No API definitions or implementation. |
| **backend.md** | Server-side behavior and architecture: system overview, API contracts, data models, business rules, validation, auth, error handling, integrations. No UI or product rationale. |
| **frontend.md** | Frontend architecture and behavior. Leave blank until frontend planning begins. |
| **file-structure.md** | Codebase organization: directory layout, module boundaries, file responsibilities, and per-function (name, responsibility, inputs, outputs, side effects, example usage). No business reasoning, flow, or execution history. |
| **progress.md** | Development execution state: work breakdown (tasks, status, blockers), implementation notes (decisions, PRD deviations, refactors), repeated errors & resolutions. Changelog lives at repo root in **CHANGELOG.md**. Update progress right after implementation; update CHANGELOG.md for user-visible or notable changes. |
| **project-status.md** | Major capability readiness table: Capability | Status | Notes. Status: Not Started, In Progress, Live, Deprecated. |

### Supporting / reference docs

| Document | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| **agent-tools-reference.md** | MCP tool reference: payloads, samples, per-agent tool lists; single source for LLM tool descriptions. |
| **data-manager-agent.md** | Data Manager Agent design: collection, distribution, CLI, triggers; no duplication of backend system overview. |
| **fund-data-schema.md** | Fund data schema: JSON fields and DB mapping for datasets/funds; companion to data-manager-agent. |
| **test_plan.md** | Test matrix and docs-consistency checklist; references progress for slice context. |
| **demo.md** | How to run demo mode and troubleshoot; module layout in file-structure. |
| **use-case-trace-beginner.md** | Step-by-step function trace for one beginner request (debugging/onboarding). |

**Generated:** **api-test-results.md** is produced by `scripts/test_third_party_apis.py`; operational only, not edited by hand.

## Update triggers (when to touch which doc)

- **user-flow.md:** New screen/state, navigation or auth flow change, error path change, new entry point.
- **prd.md:** New feature approved, scope/acceptance criteria/business requirements/success metrics change.
- **backend.md:** API contracts, data models, business rules, auth, integrations, validation change.
- **frontend.md:** When frontend architecture, components, or state management are defined.
- **file-structure.md:** New module, changed file responsibility, function added/removed/refactored, directory structure change.
- **progress.md:** Task completed/created, architectural decision, recurring error identified, behavioral change from a fix, dependency change. Update right after implementation. For **changelog entries** (features, fixes, refactors), update **CHANGELOG.md** at repo root.
- **project-status.md:** Capability becomes operational, state change, deprecated, or release milestone.
- **agent-tools-reference.md:** MCP tools added/removed/renamed or payload contract changed; keep in sync with llm/tool_descriptions.py.
- **data-manager-agent.md:** Data Manager design, CLI, or trigger behavior changed.
- **fund-data-schema.md:** Fund JSON or DB schema for datasets/funds changed.
- **test_plan.md:** Stage/test matrix or docs checklist updated.
- **demo.md:** Demo run steps or troubleshooting changed.
- **use-case-trace-beginner.md:** Request flow or function sequence for the traced path changed.

## Governance

A feature is not complete until: PRD reflects it, User Flow reflects the interaction, Backend reflects implementation, File Structure reflects code, Progress logs the change, Project Status reflects capability state. Documentation integrity is mandatory.
